   HALOE instrument image

The Halogen Occultation Experiment (HALOE) was launched on the Upper
Atmosphere Research Satellite UARS spacecraft September 12, 1991 as part of
the Earth Science Enterprise (ESE) Program. The experiment uses solar
occultation to measure vertical profiles of Ozone (O3), Hydrogen Chloride
(HCl), Hydrogen Fluoride (HF), Methane (CH4), Water (H2O), Nitric Oxide (NO),
Nitrogen Dioxide (NO2), Aerosol Extinction, Aerosol Surface and Temperature
versus pressure with an instantaneous field of view of 1.6 km at the earth
limb.
